gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 123, Warriors 115
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the Warriors, 123-115. Kevin Durant recorded 32 points and eight rebounds for the Suns, his 5th straight 30+ point game, while Devin Booker added 25 points, eight rebounds, and 10 assists in the victory. Klay Thompson tallied a season-high 23 points and six 3PM for the Warriors in the losing effort. The Suns have won five consecutive games as they improve to 9-6 on the season, while the Warriors fall to 7-9.
